  "summary": {
    "as": "Passed House",
    "asOf": "2022-04-05",
    "date": "2022-04-18T16:05:52Z",
    "text": "Spectrum Coordination Act\n\nThis bill requires the National Telecommunications and Information Administration and the Federal Communications Commission to update the Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) on Spectrum Coordination to (1) improve the process for resolving frequency allocation disputes in shared or adjacent spectrum bands, (2) ensure the efficient use of spectrum, and (3) establish reasonable timelines for information exchanges between the administration and the commission.\n\nThe MOU formalizes the cooperative relationship between the two parties to ensure that spectrum policy decisions promote efficient use of spectrum consistent with both the economic interests and national security of the nation."
  },
